+# Review — PublicMenu `x.jsx` — 2026-03-26
+
+Scope reviewed: `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx` plus page-folder context from `README.md` and `BUGS.md`, per task instructions.
+
+## Findings
+1. [P3] PM-148 removal is not enforced in `x.jsx` — the main menu still renders `ModeTabs` with `verifiedByCode`, `currentTableId`, `currentTable`, and `resolvedTable` at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3371-3384`. This file does not add an explicit guard that disables the post-verification success/banner path after table-code confirmation. FIX: remove the banner-driving prop/path from the menu render in `x.jsx`, or pass an explicit "do not show confirmation banner" flag while preserving the bottom-sheet flow.
+2. [P3] Guest-facing name output is still unsanitized in `x.jsx` — `getGuestDisplayName` is passed directly to `CartView` at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3519-3530`, and the same helper is used for the hall-order confirmation label at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2772-2774` and `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3478-3481`. This file does not strip the trailing ` #N` suffix for guest-facing UI. FIX: format the display string in `x.jsx` before passing/rendering it, stripping a trailing `\\s+#\\d+$` while leaving underlying guest data unchanged.
+
+## Summary
+- Total findings: 2
+- Priority split: 0 P0, 0 P1, 0 P2, 2 P3
+- Prompt clarity: 4/5
